stream
BT /F1 9.5 Tf 54 713.00 Td (Meaning:) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.5 Tf 54 688.00 Td (- FPGA/HSB path is working.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.5 Tf 54 675.50 Td (- Camera sensor is not responding over I2C.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.5 Tf 54 663.00 Td (- On early production Agilex 5 MDK boards, this can be caused by the carrier MAX10 firmware not) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.5 Tf 54 650.50 Td (  applying power to the MIPI connectors.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.5 Tf 54 638.00 Td (- Without MIPI connector power, camera I2C communication is impossible and Holoscan applications) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.5 Tf 54 625.50 Td (  report transaction errors.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.5 Tf 54 600.50 Td (Checks performed:) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.5 Tf 54 575.50 Td (- Camera cable orientation.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.5 Tf 54 563.00 Td (- Pin 1 to pin 1 alignment.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.5 Tf 54 550.50 Td (- Correct MIPI connector.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.5 Tf 54 538.00 Td (- Camera power/reset sequencing.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.5 Tf 54 525.50 Td (- Reprogram FPGA after camera connection.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.5 Tf 54 500.50 Td (Root cause found during this bring-up:) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.5 Tf 54 475.50 Td (- Early production MDK boards, both Group A and Group B, shipped with a bug in the MAX10 image.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.5 Tf 54 463.00 Td (- The buggy MAX10 image does not apply power to the MIPI connectors.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.5 Tf 54 450.50 Td (- Customer release production boards are expected to ship with the fixed MAX10 image and should be) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.5 Tf 54 438.00 Td (  plug-and-play.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.5 Tf 54 425.50 Td (- Currently available / early boards may need the MAX10 image reflashed.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.5 Tf 54 400.50 Td (Resolution that fixed the camera I2C transaction errors:) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.5 Tf 54 375.50 Td (1. Switch the MAX10 onto the JTAG chain by setting SW4 on the carrier board to ON. This is the single) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.5 Tf 54 363.00 Td (  switch nearest the HDMI connector.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.5 Tf 54 350.50 Td (2. Use Quartus Programmer GUI to reflash MAX10 with:) Tj ET
BT /F3 8 Tf 54 313.00 Td (   max10_top_rtl_v1p1p6_fw_v2p0p1.pof) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.5 Tf 54 277.50 Td (3. Power off the board.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.5 Tf 54 265.00 Td (4. To see the FPGA on the JTAG chain again, set SW4 back to OFF.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.5 Tf 54 240.00 Td (After reflashing the MAX10 image and restoring the normal JTAG chain, camera I2C configuration) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.5 Tf 54 227.50 Td (  succeeded.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.5 Tf 54 202.50 Td (Additional note:) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.5 Tf 54 177.50 Td (- A problem with initial production MDK batches is that the USB hub controlling the carrier micro USB) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.5 Tf 54 165.00 Td (  is susceptible to ESD.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.5 Tf 54 152.50 Td (- This is expected to be resolved in future batches.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.5 Tf 54 140.00 Td (- If the carrier micro USB is not detected, for example Windows fails to read descriptors, use the) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.5 Tf 54 127.50 Td (  standard JTAG connector and a Byte Blaster instead.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.5 Tf 54 102.50 Td (Successful camera configuration log:) Tj ET
BT /F3 8 Tf 54 65.00 Td (Configuring camera with frame format: Width=1920, Height=1080, Framerate=30, Pixel ) Tj ET
endstream
